funcatron.intf

Interface Constants


  • public interface Constants
    Constants related to Funcatron. For all Functions associated with finding or setting named functions of certain types, here are the named functions along with the expected function signature. Note that function signatures with Void as a parameter mean that the parameter is ignored and null should be passed.

      • ConvertGetSwaggerFunc

        static final Function<BiFunction<Map<Object,Object>,Logger,Object>,BiFunction<Void,Logger,Map<String,Object>>> ConvertGetSwaggerFunc
        The type signature for the getSwagger function. The return Map should have two entries: "type" which is one of "json", "yaml", or "map" and the entry for "swagger". If the "type" is "json", the "swagger" entry should be a String which is parsed as JSON. If the "type" is "yaml", the "swagger" entry should be a String which is parsed using a YAML parser. If the "type" is "map", the "swagger" field should be a Map<String, Object> that contains the parsed Swagger.

      • ConvertDispatcherForFunc

        static final Function<BiFunction<Map<Object,Object>,Logger,Object>,BiFunction<Map<Object,Object>,Logger,BiFunction<InputStream,Map<Object,Object>,Map<Object,Object>>>> ConvertDispatcherForFunc
        Given the Swagger entry for an endpoint, return the dispatcher for that entry. The "$operationId" field contains the operationId associated with the endpoint. The rest of the endpoint definition is the rest of the map. The "$deserializer" field contains the built in deserializer function. The "$serializer" function.
        The returned function performs the dispatch for the endpoint where the InputStream is the request body, the Map is the request information. The function returns a response Map that must have the "status", "headers", and "body" fields set.

      • ConvertGetSerializerFunc

        static final Function<BiFunction<Map<Object,Object>,Logger,Object>,BiFunction<Map<Object,Object>,Logger,BiFunction<Object,String,byte[]>>> ConvertGetSerializerFunc
        Return a function that will take a response object, a mime type, and return a byte[] representing the bytes to return. If null is returned, then the built-in serializer will be used.

      • ConvertGetDeserializerFunc

        static final Function<BiFunction<Map<Object,Object>,Logger,Object>,BiFunction<Map<Object,Object>,Logger,BiFunction<InputStream,List<Object>,Object>>> ConvertGetDeserializerFunc
        Return a function that performs deserialization of an InputStream into a reified Object. The return function takes the the InputStream which is the request body and a List<Object> where the first entries are a String with the contentType and a Class<?> paramType
